Direct Access
Direct access also works as an means to communicate from UI side
back to backend. One could use Event communication for everything
but since we already save the references for easier refresh it make
sense to use it here as well. Another advantage to event based approach
is that we dont need to use two events calls (pls send new data and send
data)
(Used for button click value go change in backend)
Each Widget has a reference to its personal Widget
Controller. Through which we communicate from UI side
back to controller which then forwards the logic to backend

Direct Access
It doesnt realy matter where the data are from our middle man
Widget Controller just needs to hookup into provided events and take a
reference from which we can use for direct access.
Gameplay Message
Subsystem
Gameplay Message Subsystem GMS for short is an module that implements the global
observer pattern using combination of gameplay tags and message struct (payload) to
send events and listen to event not limited for UI only. It's really quite handy and I recommend
using it for decoupled communication. One could completely bypass the widget controller and just listen
for events on Widget side but I think its better to have a centralised place (controller in this case)
where all the communication happens.
Bound Events
Bound events are the classic unreal bind/unbind events that are used throughout
the code base and its used here the same way as normally.
Here we use only GMS to have one universal approach and the ability to
start and stop listening to input based on activation
